<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Dearest Littany,<br>
<br>
I trust Tanare's stay with you thus far has been pleasant?  I'm sure you'd know if it hasn't.  She can get in such a fret over her fingernails.<br>
<br>
Anywho, I just write to check up on the young Ranger.  A solution to this problem of ours might be at hand.  I just hope you keep the Ranger in good shape before she returns to us, as I'd hate to have to deal with the mob of Hair Dressers and other beauticians we'd have to tolerate in the guildhall for a few days if not.<br>
<br>
Take good care of her, and I've had this bard bring with him a Fruit Pie for her.  You're welcome to a slice yourself if you want.<br>
<br>
Smirkingly Yours,<br>
Zippus Maximor<br>
Arcanist of the Greatfool<br>
<br>
P.S. ~ Sergian sends his regards, and his love to Tanare.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Smirkingly ever slightly at the last line of his letter, he folds it and dribbles a bit of wax on the fold-line.  Pressing his Gear Shaped Emblem into the Wax, he seals it and hands it, along with a Fruit Pie (which, he notes, smells delicious) to the Bard at the door.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is going to get interesting...&quot; He mumbles, before going off to seek the 2nd Pie he aquired...for himself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olmembar>OlmEmbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/5/03 9:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> D'RonKarr sat at the bar in the tavern located across from the necromancer's guild grounds.  <br>
 He had completed his guard duty quite a few hours ago and then gone hunting to fill his packs with a few more spiderling silks and animal hides to replace the ones he had given to Tanare.   <br>
While the repeated mowing down of such animals was good exercise to keep him in shape for possable future battles, that knowledge did not aid him with what he was thinking.   <br>
His muscle aches and pains were par for the course,  the growing pain in his heart was not.<br>
<br>
He picked up his mug of imported Dark Haven ale and drank it all down,  then asked for another.   <br>
The bartender took his mug away and refilled it, handing it back to him, and  he took it with a thanks.    <br>
He stared into the refreshed mug  moodily, realizing that this was starting to become a habit.   <br>
Perhaps an after effect of trying to get Tanare to develope a taste for drinking.      <br>
It was a useless thing to do, all that effort at corrupting her.   <br>
While it did indeed seem to be working nicely, what was the point?   <br>
<br>
Then a fellow from the Necropolisis just  had to ask &quot;D'Ron, Is the elf ranger dead yet?&quot;<br>
He promptly downed the whole mug.<br>
She was growing on him he realized.<br>
&quot;No.&quot;  He mumbled as he found his head nodding and trying to meet the counter.<br>
&quot;Pretty little  bubblie sweet thing gets to be dead at Moondark.&quot;  He thought he said but the others around him just shrugged not understanding the reply.   <br>
Bleary eyed he did not ask for another drink but simply watched and listened to the skeletal band as they played their music.<br>
<br>
Several hours later the Acolyte found him.   &quot;D'RonKarr, you are ordered to report to High Priestess Littany immediately.   She has been waiting all afternoon and evening to talk to you, and grows impatient.  He gave a sigh and stood up.  The hour was late, whatever it was must indeed be important that it couldn't wait until morning or as he arrived for guard duty .   He followed behind the Acolyte as they made their way back to the Temple. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhaxalygen>Rhaxalygen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 329<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/5/03 12:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> (Ooh, this story is HILARIOUS! Can I join in somehow?)<br>
