<br>
 Littany tells temple:3, '*enters the room, seeing Dronkarr waiting, she does not offer wine, or refreshments, but just stands, her eye boring into him'<br>
 <br>
DRonKarr looks at the High Priestess groggly and says 'Yes Mistress, er High Priestess Littany?'<br>
<br>
 Littany says, 'so Dronkarr (( voice smooth as ice')),&quot;'what have you been doing as of late?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'A lot of hunting Priestess.'<br>
<br>
 Littany says, 'xas? is this all?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'Many orcs and well, spiderlings and cats and bears have fallen to my blades'<br>
<br>
 Littany's voice purrs a little, with a slightly unpleasent edge', &quot; 'DronKarr, you swore to serve the temple Xas?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says 'Ummm, I have displeased you somehow?'......Yes, and I have performed my turns at guard duty as you have wished.'<br>
<br>
 Littany says,  'have you seen our captive Knight?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says 'Captive knight?  No, I cannot say I have.'<br>
<br>
Littany says 'and does her fear grow?..... 'and do you help her Know the God?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'I have not not visited the dungeons'    'Oh, you are talking about the ranger?'<br>
<br>
 Littany says, 'do not play the fool Dronkarr, I will not be served by fools.  Do you wish to confess to me your sins?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron lifts an eye brow.   'I have many....'<br>
<br>
 Littany says, '*hisses* xas, you do at that, and you will do penance, do you not think that Cazic sees all in his temple.  How you coddle the woodelf, how you pamper her?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'Ah, well, you said you wanted her unassuming.   And that you were going to inspire fear in her.'<br>
<br>
 Littany says, 'and you shall now help in this *smiles*.  You will tell her who you are Knight, what you are.  And do so in a manner to help her know of Fear'<br>
<br>
D'Ron remains silent for a minute.<br>
<br>
 Littany says, 'or, could it be you are weak, 'that you cannot stomach the service of Our Lord?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron scowls.  'You think me weak for not terrorizing a sacrificial lamb ahead of time?'<br>
<br>
 Littany says , 'are you capable of such? words mean little to me Knight'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'What do you have in mind, or do you wish to leave that entirely to me?'<br>
<br>
Littany says, 'I leave it to your creativity, but know this'<br>
 Littany tells temple:3, 'I will naut have you coddling her again'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'Getting her drunk is coddeling?'   'I would have liked to get her to like it....but ...'<br>
<br>
 Littany says, 'you know what I mean *snaps*'<br>
<br>
D'Ron remains silent.<br>
<br>
Littany comands, 'now GO.   <br>
Do naut disappoint me again'<br>
Or the moondark will see more than one serve Thule'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'Yes, Priestess....In what condition must she be left in...intact before the sacrifice...'<br>
<br>
 Littany frowns* Do not seek to quench your lust with my prey '<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'No beatings either I take it.'<br>
<br>
 Littany says, 'Fear is not served by the torment of the flesh .. but of the mind'.  Do you naut learn anything from this?<br>
The body does not need breaking, the mind is the key'<br>
'I leave to the crude Iksar, and the Trolls to serve Fear by such crude means, we, you and I , we serve the God with more refinement'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says, 'I, am used to breaking the mind by breaking the body....I will have to learn more, and yes, your will, will be done'<br>
<br>
 Littany says, 'now go *a gesture of dismissal*  I have much to do'<br>
Do not Fail me Knight'<br>
Do not fail Our Lord'<br>
<br>
D'Ron Karr bows and turns around to leave.   'Yes Priestess.'<br>
<br>
 '&lt;Exits&gt;'<br>
---------------<br>
<br>
D'RonKarr walks out into the courtyard and takes a deep lungfull of rain freshened air, then peers up into the sky, looking at nothing in particular.&gt;'<br>
His desire for much need sleep temporarily twarted<br>
 'He then sits down on the rim of one of the many fountains and places his head in his hands.<br>
<br>
He thinks to himself,  '*I knew I was going to have to show myself as what i actually am to her, why should it bother me so much now?*'<br>
 '*I will indeed have to think on this<br>
&lt;Stands back up and makes his way back to his quarters&gt;'<br>
 '&lt;Where he lays down on his bed and stares up at the ceiling.&gt;'<br>
 '*Well I guess I was really becoming somwhat attached to her.  Maybe I am weak.   I will have to be carefull.*'<br>
