&quot;good&quot; meaning &quot;serving Tunare most faithfully and <br>
having the proper desire to see anyone thoroughly<br>
dead who dared spoil the beautiful lands of Norrath.&quot; <br>
<br>
Now, however, in her 12th season of tracking and<br>
hunting, Aurwena was not &quot;good&quot; anymore, nor<br>
did she consider herself so. She had turned to<br>
a mixed triad of deities--Rallos Zek, Veeshan, and<br>
Zeboxurok, the Forsaken, instead of Tunare. She<br>
did not hate the Mother of All; rather, Aurwena<br>
simply believed that the gods of War, Wyrmkind,<br>
and Wanderers better suited her personality.<br>
<br>
Her apostasy, as the Clerics of Tunare liked to call it,<br>
started when Aurwena realized she had no desire<br>
to exterminate the Orcs of Crushbone. In the time<br>
before her exile, her first year, the young Ranger<br>
thought that this lack of zeal to kill the Orcs was<br>
due to her belief that any kind of genocide was stupid.<br>
However, she soon realized that Rallos Zek was <br>
calling her to himself, even as a Kelethin Ranger.<br>
Killing Orcs was killing the children of Zek, and<br>
with her growing affinity for Rallos, Aurwena dared not.<br>
<br>
Thus, the first deity that she worshipped with all<br>
devotion was Rallos Zek, the Warlord, for ever <br>
since her banishment from Kelethin, she had <br>
spent her life growing strong and ferocious<br>
in battle, invigorated by the thrill of the hunt. <br>
<br>
She soon learned to follow Zeboxurok as well, the<br>
Despised, also the patron of exiles. As for Veeshan--<br>
Aurwena never had wanted to kill the gentle forest<br>
drakelings and drakes that came her way. Strange--<br>
she was called to her gods by the creatures that <br>
she DIDN'T want to hunt down! Such was her fate<br>
following the Mixed Triad, fighting for her own life...<br>
<br>
...and then, in Qeynos, Aurwena instinctively felt the <br>
call of one of her fellow Rangers, far away, whose life<br>
was in grave danger. She didn't know it yet, but this<br>
young Wood Elf, whose name was--Tanare, yes?--<br>
was destined to die on the altar of her Mother's enemy, <br>
Cazic-Thule, if someone didn't do something fast!<br>
<br>
&quot;I shall try and rescue you,&quot; Aurwena whispered to the<br>
wind, &quot;even though I'm only 12 and lack the proper <br>
experience to defeat your captors in battle head-on!&quot;<br>
<br>
Thus she strode to Paineel, where Aurwena had fought<br>
before, against the flea-ridden, growling Kobolds in the<br>
Warrens. However, once the young Ranger had snuck<br>
past the scowling skeletal guards and Noclin Saah, <br>
the scowling necromancer standing watch over the<br>
Paineel yard, and gotten to the entrance of the <br>
Warrens, Aurwena realized, out of breath, that<br>
she was out of luck. If she tried to rescue Tanare,<br>
she would be slaughtered faster than a rabid kobold!<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, Zek, now what am I to do?&quot; she grumbled, chiding<br>
herself for her foolhardy plans. &quot;I don't even have Camouflage yet, so how in the world am I going to<br>
rescue this poor girl? This is the stupidest thing I've<br>
ever done, besides telling the Kelethin Guards that I<br>
now follow the Mixed Triad and getting exiled!&quot;  <br>
<br>
She sighed, taking a drink of water from the pool<br>
outside the Warrens, and waited for any bright ideas<br>
to come to her from her gods. None came, however,<br>
and soon Aurwena was forced to send out an instinctive message to see if Tanare, the prisoner, would respond. <br>
<br>
&quot;Tanare,&quot; she whispered, &quot;if you can hear me, sense<br>
me, or have any inkling at all that I'm here, I want to<br>
tell you that I'm a Wood Elf, and a fellow Ranger. I've<br>
come to rescue you, by the gods, even if it means I<br>
get slaughtered like a kobold! My name is Aurwena,<br>
and I want to know if you're still alive,&quot; she prayed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tanare>Tanare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/6/03 9:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1>  Tanare sat at the table, a confused look on her face as she stared at the mirror this morning. Yesterday's mirror which she knew had to come from the gypsy camp was gone and another was in its place.<br>
<br>
   In its reflection she saw herself sitting down dejectedly, a sad look on her face as if she had been crushed down by the wieght of the world. A look of hopelessness in her eyes asher reflection sat, clad in the crudest of garments as if waiting for another to tell her what she should do and not moving until she had gained such instructions. A haunted beaten look stared back from the image's eyes at the young ranger who sat before it.<br>
<br>
   Tanare's brow wrinkled in an unusual furrow of deep thought as she attempted to figure out what this could mean. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Does this mean the dress i'm going to get is like..ugly or something and i'm like sad cause i waited all this time for nothing? And like my eyes get all baggy from trying to stay awake and see when they'll be ready for my fitting? Maybe Dronky might know even though he was just here yesterday with the gypsy mirror. This one's no fun.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> she thought to herself.<br>
<br>
  She concentrated again at the mirror's image before and finally came to her conclusion. &quot;I don't get it.&quot; Despairing at being able to comb her hair today she looked to the door hopeful that an army of tailors would come and get her dress prepared. Suddenly remembering something else she picked up some of the pelts still lying on the floor and again attempted to figure out how she would combine this spider silk in her pack to the bear pelt in her hands. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Wait til i mkae like an even cuter dress than the bigforeheady peoples do, that'll show them not to be so slow and stuff.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> she decided as she concentrated on her work. Faintly she heard a dim echo but the only two words she could pick out were &quot;ranger&quot; and &quot;rescue&quot;<br>
<br>
   <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Awww some poor person is like in trouble and stuff. Well since there's already a mighty and tough ranger there to save them i can keep sewing.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> she concluded as she ruined the bear pelt before with her sewing needles. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> It was nice of all these cute wolfies and kitties and teddy bears to like give me their pelts to do my sewing on cause they knew i like needed practice and stuff, i hope it all will grow back before it like gets cold and stuff.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
   The tip of her tongue again poking out the side of her mouth unnoticed as she turned back to her task at hand Tanare sewed on, still oblivious as to what was going on.<br>
