<br>
As he stepped out of the temple corridor, having ungracefully vented his lungs, D'Ron Karr relieved one of the guards standing just outside the doors.   It was his turn at guard duty, and the lengthy, and fruitless attempt to converse and inspire fear in the wood elven ranger had almost made him late.  He turned down one of the skeletal guard's invitation to join them in a game of dice and just stood, attempting to relax by listening to the thunder and breathing in the ozone laden air.   It seemed more stimulating than relaxing.  He felt he needed to go and vent himself on some koblods.  <br>
<br>
As he continued to stand there, he began to think of the sand elf head bouncing around.  Then he thought of Tanare  with purple, pink, or green hair.  He grinned.  Naw, she probably would just rationalize it away.  Shaved all off maybe.  No, better yet, a load of quick setting clayish dirt loaded into it, and no way to wash it out for months....Broken fingernails,  horse manure....swamp water...anything 'Icky!'<br>
<br>
He glanced over at the skeletons playing with their dice and cards, then settled himself somemore, still standing at semi-attention.  It was going to be a long day.<br>
