the Warrens, waiting for any instinctive vibes or echoes<br>
from the prisoner, Tanare, and trying to figure out what<br>
to do about sneaking into Paineel. As she was only 13,<br>
the young Wood Elf could not cast the Camouflage spell yet, but there was no way, by Zek, that she would let Tanare die so that she herself could gain experience!<br>
<br>
At last, she heard an instinctive echo coming from <br>
Tanare, and it was not a good one. Tanare, it seemed,<br>
believed that SHE, Aurwena, was in trouble, and not<br>
herself! Aurwena sent a vibe back, limiting it to <br>
as few words as possible, in case the mountain air<br>
in Paineel was too tainted by evil for detailed echoes.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're in danger! I will help soon!&quot; That was the vibe. <br>
<br>
After sending out this echo through the Paineel yard and down into the city, Aurwena sighed and meditated a bit, regaining her mana for some potentially huge battles, when another Ranger, a Human, and a Cleric entered<br>
the outside foyer of the Warrens. Aurwena asked:<br>
<br>
&quot;Could one of you please cast a spell of invisibility over<br>
me so I could try to enter Paineel without being seen?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Which spell do you want?&quot; asked the Cleric, a tall Human male dressed in pale green armour, the livery<br>
of Rodcet Nife. &quot;Invisibility versus Undead, or my <br>
Ranger friend's Camouflage spell?&quot; The Ranger was<br>
also a Human, a female, wearing a dark green leather suit of Pine Scout armor found in Surefall Glade. <br>
<br>
&quot;I'll take Camouflage,&quot; Aurwena answered. &quot;I know you can't have Invisibility versus Undead and Camouflage<br>
cast over you at the same time and have them both hold, so I'll see if I can sneak by the Erudites in Paineel while trying to avoid their undead servant guards.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Suit yourself,&quot; said the Ranger, who exhibited a red aura before Aurwena's eyes, &quot;but if I were you, I would<br>
gain more seasons of experience killing Kobolds and then see if I could enter Paineel safely.&quot; She smiled. <br>
&quot;Killing Kobolds raises faction with the Heretics there.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I know,&quot; said Aurwena humbly, &quot;but this is an emergency--a dire one! One of my fellow Wood Elves<br>
is in mortal danger. Could you, perhaps--help me rescue her?&quot; This was a shot in the dark, for the Ranger and the Cleric were strangers, but it might be her only chance...<br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry,&quot; said the Ranger with a shrug. &quot;We're headed for the Warrens to slaughter some Kobolds ourselves, so we can't help you. I can give you Camo, though,&quot; said<br>
the Human Scout as she cast the spell over Aurwena.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you,&quot; said the Wood Elf, &quot;and good hunting!&quot; She watched the two disappear through the tunnel into the Kobolds' lair, and then Aurwena climbed the stairs<br>
that led back through the yard. &quot;Here goes,&quot; she said.<br>
Aurwena ran right through the center of the gate, for<br>
the skeleton guards' aggression radius was quite low,<br>
and then she paused. Now was the point of no return.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tanare, good Ranger, I'll rescue you, or die trying!&quot; <br>
Aurwena took a deep breath, summoning all the courage<br>
that the Mixed Triad could give her, and then entered the damp, dark lair of a meditating Cleric or Necromancer.<br>
