League of Shadows<br>
Paineel<br>
<br>
Dear D'Ron Karr,<br>
<br>
We met once, I am not sure if you remember.  At that time you seemed a paladin.. Perhaps one who could so convincingly play this part has a little of such in truth hidden inside him.<br>
<br>
I know it is a longshot writing to you, but I have nothing to lose. Last night I met with Littany, and her demands are more than can be met. But in the conversation, I learned that it was by your hand that Tanare was delivered to Paineel.<br>
<br>
I know you serve the Temple D'Ron, and I will not insult you by suggesting that you do anything which would harm your mistress or betray your guild and faith.  I just would beg one favour, that I might meet with Tanare once more before the moondark, and bid my ward fare well. I know one such as you would be insulted by the offer of gold or gems for such a boon. I would offer instead my word, that you would have a geas on me. That you could call upon me in the future for a like favour, and if it was in my power I would grant it. <br>
<br>
Yours in hope<br>
<br>
Meledi Weaver<br>
League of Honour <p><img border=0 src="http://www.leagueofhonour.com/images/members/meledi-sig.jpg" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olmembar>OlmEmbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/03 12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A letter to Tanare</span><hr size=1> D'Ron Karr shifted his position and reached into his back pack, removing his spell book and a piece of parchment and pen.   Using the back of his spell book as an impromptu table, he began to write.<br>
<br>
Dear Tanare,<br>
<br>
Since it is your wish that I write letters, I will do so, this one is for you.<br>
<br>
First of all, I must say that I really did enjoy hunting with you and it was a pleasure seeing how you so adeptly dispatched the multitudes of Trogs and then later the Kobolds. <br>
 Such enthusiam.  Such courageousness, such  lack of fear.   It is too bad you were not born a dark elf. <br>
I even began to enjoy your conversations.  I never knew one could make so very much of so very little.  <br>
And your nievity about your situation, enertaining at first, but, it is to your own detriment &lt;scratched out&gt;, bad luck, danger to you.<br>
   <br>
I write because I still hold hope for you to come to an understanding of the situation that you are in.<br>
Perhaps with this written down, it will be easier for you to understand.  <br>
I will try and present the facts that, if you pay attention and reason them out, are obvious.  And should be so even for you.  <br>
<br>
First of all, saying you do not believe something will not make that something go away, nor change it.  If you step out into a street infront of an oncoming carrage....and say 'I do not believe it is there'   will you not still end up just as flattened as if you did believe it was there?  <br>
If you are warned that there is a trap in the path ahead, a pit covered over with branches and dirt, will you still walk on top of it and fall in to your death?<br>
<br>
I will list some facts for you.<br>
<br>
1.   Paladins do not summon, call or free skeletons,  except to  'smite' them to send their spirits on their way.<br>
<br>
2.  Paladins do not lead others into the temples of the gods called: <br>
Innoruuk,<br>
Cazic Thule<br>
Bertoxxulous<br>
except to wage war upon those who follow these gods.<br>
<br>
3.  The city of Paineel is known as the city of Heratics, the god honored here is Cazic Thule, and is home to the shadowknights and necromancers of the Erudian race.  That is undoubtedly why your 'Sergy' never showed you this city.<br>
<br>
4.  You are in the temple of Cazic Thule.<br>
<br>
5.  The Lady that greeted you here is Littany D'Thule,  a High Priestess of Cazic Thule.    She told you this.<br>
<br>
6.  D'RonKarr placed shackles on your wrists, the kind that cannot be removed unless unlocked, and the chain from them is attached to the wall of the temple, keeping you from leaving.  Attached there by the High Priestess.<br>
<br>
7.  The High Priestess Littany  also called your league the false league.<br>
<br>
8.  High Priestess LIttany D'Thule told you that you would be staying with us until the Moondark, at which time there would be a party and you would have a new dress to wear.   She also told you that you were the guest of Lord Thule.  <br>
<br>
9.  Lord Cazic Thule is known as the God of Fear.<br>
<br>
10.  The sacrifice of a young person is needed for the dedication of a new Temple to Cazic Thule to replace the one that Meledi had burned down along with the city of Necropolis.  <br>
<br>
11.  You are to be that sacrifice. <br>
Sacrifice means a ritual in which one is killed.<br>
<br>
12.  The sacrificual ritual is the 'party' of which High Priestess Littany was refering to .<br>
<br>
13.  The dress she is making for you is to  be the robe you will wear at this ceramony.<br>
<br>
14.  You are the 'guest of honor' at this ceramony, meaning that you are the main subject to be killed.<br>
<br>
These are the facts, these are the truths.  Not facing up to them by fantisizing &lt;scratched out&gt;, pretending to yourself that there are two D'Ron Karrs will not change these facts.<br>
<br>
I am D'Ron Karr, the shadowknight that pretended to be a paladin in order to lead you to Littany D'Thule and your death  in dedicating the new temple.  <br>
<br>
Know this, even though my god is Innoruuk, I have taken a blood oath to serve Littany and protect and serve her temple, and I will not abandoned that oath.  So if it is any satisfaction to you, you may as well know that I will probably be at your side for the ceramonies of this ritual, as I have failed at the task assigned to me.<br>
<br>
Perhaps if you understand your situation you will even come to see your part in this as a great  honor.   <br>
After all, only a few ever get chosen for the purpose of dedicating new temples.<br>
And it seems to me as if you are actually trying to volunteer for this.<br>
But to truely volunteer for this honor, <br>
you need to be aware of your surroundings, where you are.  And that, is in the Temple of Cazic Thule.<br>
<br>
Perhaps I will be able to visit you again before Moondark, we shall see.<br>
<br>
Your paladin/shadowknight.  D'RonKarr<br>
<br>
----------------<br>
<br>
D'Ron waited for the ink to dry then rolled up the parchment and sealed it.  He placed it into his pack and stood up.   Guard duty finished, he decided he would take a long walk into Steamfont, and would catch the local bard later, after he returned.<br>
 <br>
<br>
<br>
