through the blessings of the Mixed Triad--Zek, Zeboxurok,<br>
and Veeshan--heard Tanare's shout as clearly as if the<br>
young prisoner had been standing right next to her. <br>
Aurwena herself knew she was still only 14, and, thus,<br>
she could not reach Tanare unless someone offered <br>
her another Camouflage spell very soon. She sighed.<br>
<br>
Luckily, the meditating Cleric, who seemed to go by<br>
the name of Azzar, didn't notice the sudden exhaling<br>
of breath, for it wasn't very loud. Also, when you're<br>
deep in meditation, you hardly notice anything. <br>
<br>
Sensing great fright within herself, Aurwena prayed, &quot;Zek,<br>
I am afraid! Fear is not something you relish in your own<br>
servants, I know, but true courage is doing something <br>
DESPITE one's fear, not in total ABSENCE of one's fear.&quot;<br>
<br>
Again, Azzar the Cleric did not hear, standing silent and still.<br>
<br>
Considering the message Tanare had given her, Aurwena<br>
was drawing a shocking conclusion: &quot;She thinks she's in<br>
the Bazaar, or one of the good/neutral towns that sells her<br>
pretty dresses! She doesn't realize she's in danger, and<br>
even though I tried to convince her, apparently she doesn't<br>
believe it! I shall have to come up with another way to  persuade her to try and escape Paineel. Ah!  I know!&quot; <br>
<br>
Sending out another instinctive message through the <br>
channel of her soul, Aurwena said, &quot;I know a shop where<br>
I live that sells lots of pretty dresses, and they're MUCH<br>
cheaper than the ones they sell here! Leave this place,<br>
if you can, and come with me to where I live! Be strong!&quot; <br>
<br>
Aurwena backed into the corner from where she had slunk,<br>
but just then, she sensed that the Camouflage protecting<br>
her was wearing off. Heeding the magical warning, the<br>
young Ranger moved away from where Azzar stood and<br>
snuck back into the tunnel leading to Toxxulia Forest. <br>
When her Camouflage wore off, Aurwena hoped that<br>
Tanare had heard her message and would try to escape. <br>
<br>
Fear coursed through her. What, by Zek, would she do now? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olmembar>OlmEmbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/14/03 3:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A letter</span><hr size=1> (/ooc Eeep!   That's supposed to be Stonebrunt, not Steamfont...how do you  edit these posts?) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olmembar>OlmEmbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/16/03 9:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A Walk</span><hr size=1> ((Thought about it and then decided to go ahead and post this, hope Lopo does not mind))<br>
---------<br>
<br>
D'RonKarr says:  &quot;I sit here, pondering life, as I watch the waves lap against the sides of a fine ship.<br>
<br>
Draknor says: &quot;What art dos doing in Stonebrunt?&quot;<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,   'I sit on the shores, on a cliffside above a fine ship, watching the waves lap against it as the sands of time flow by, and ponder on life.'<br>
<br>
Lopothandilius says:  &quot;So this means that you are fishing.;<br>
<br>
D'Ronsays,  'Nay, just staring at the waves.'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'What has dos in such an internal search?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'Do you really wish to know?<br>
<br>
Lopo says,    'Ustan would naut have asked otherwise.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,   'I have failed at an important task that High Priestess Littany assigned to me.   <br>
I have found myself as haveing become attracted to one I should have not, though her brainlessness has helped against this attraction somewhat.  <br>
I am weak and I have failed.'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,   'Dos.... had better naut have fallen in love with an elf.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'Aye.....became too close to what I was guarding....and found myself protecting her for other reasons.'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,    '..........'<br>
Lopo says,    'Guarding -- und this was the task dos also failed Lady Littany at?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,   'Hence, the long walk in the fresh air.<br>
No, she (Tanare) has, and will be, guarded well.  <br>
I have failed in the task of inspiring fear in her.<br>
<br>
Lopo says,   'By succumbing to her charms.<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,   'She is as brainless and as innocent as a new born baby.<br>
<br>
Lopo says,   'Her frailty art a weakness abil.   Naut something to  inspire Dosst feelings of lust.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'Not even that....succumbing to her.....bublie brainless shatter....I am weak.<br>
I am both weak ....and failed at a task.<br>
/si U wander and think of alternatives.'<br>
<br>
Lopo chuckles.  'Alternatives to what?  Dos seem to need to prove doss self to innoruuk und dosst self again.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,   'The only thing i can think of...is the one thing she fears, and I cannot physically touch her.&quot;<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'Dos art bound naut to slay her?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'Yes, that is for Littany... She must not be touched physically in any way.    And the  only way to install fear in her, I believe.....is to ...dump the dirtiest....yukiest....load of muck you could possably come up with....in her hair....'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'Dos must be joking?  Physical threats do naut scare her?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  &quot; ...and not give her anything to wash it out with.   But that...is physical too.'<br>
'No'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'Ustan do naut think Littany would object to that...it's not physical harm.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'If it were possable....She would even make a good Shadow knight.....you should have seen her glee at slaying all the Kobolds.'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'Bah, the pale rot hate the kobolds that way, not just her.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  &quot;I tossed a sand elf head towards her and she was only worried about being contaminated.   She is clueless.'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'Odd....dos should have taken her to slay elves.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'Perhaps that would be possable if she was not slated to be sacrificed.'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'Take her before that.    When is this to happen?'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'I have already had success with getting her to think she must drink to make herself stronger.   Bit it is not up to me to unchain her, she is Liggany's charge now.   <br>
I only guard her, and I have been told not to 'coddle' her, so I will be keeping my distance now.   <br>
It is better that way, least my weakness grows instead of diminishing.   <br>
But she is soo...so...STUPID!'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'She is wise to have removed dos from the situation.  <br>
At least she will be put to death.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'And better the light elf gene pool.    <br>
Bahh!  Wrong sacrifice if you want fear, right plus some, if yoou want innocence.'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  'Ustan must depart again.   Innoruuk will show dos the path of hate dos must follow.'<br>
<br>
D'Ron says,  'I am sure he will.   I have followed it well enough in the past.  <br>
Take care Lopo.'<br>
<br>
Lopo says,  &quot;Rest well abit.' <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olmembar>OlmEmbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/16/03 10:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Letter to Meledy singy person</span><hr size=1> After spending more time just watching over the ocean and the activities of the crew of the ship beneath him, D'Ron Karr stood up and began to head back to the Warrens and Paineel.  He gathered shadows around himself so as to not be bothered with the neuscence animals that wandered the hills and forrests and was shortly back to the Warrens, where he proceeded to once again slaughter any of the kobolds that happened to be in his way. <br>
<br>
Making his way back out of the warrens and towards the city he passed a young elven female with the gear of a ranger.  She looked even younger than Tanare, and as he made his way further up , he reaized that she  did not apparently have any one else accompanying her.   He made a mentel note to see if she was still there after he sent the letter off.<br>
<br>
Back in the city D'Ron approached the merchant next to the bank that also kept the local news.  Here he handed him the scroll, along with an appropriate fee, not explaining as to why he was not delivering it himself.    The erudite raised an eyebrow at him, but then looking at the seal he said, <br>
'Oh, you are the one I have a letter for also.  Now I do not have to hunt for you at the temple, her you are...&quot;   And he handed D'Ron the letter from Meledi.  Puzzled, as to why he would be receiving a letter from Meledi and not Littany, he walked over to a nearby table and proceeded to read it.  <br>
<br>
Deep in thought he sat silently for a few minutes afterwards, then rolled the letter back up.   He stood up and walked over to a torch to light the end of it, then stopped.<br>
*No, I will let the High Priestess read this...perhaps she will find it useful, I will see what she desires on this manner.*  he thought to himself, and pulled the scroll away, to hold it firmly in his hand.<br>
He then headed back over to the temple to give it to her. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=1193.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=1193.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=1193.topic&start=61&stop=76>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=1193.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=1193.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.threadControl?topicID=1193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="t